    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="268"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Goodnow</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I do not think it expedient to submit! the proposition of Earl Li to the other
                    powers. Free communication with our representatives in Pekin is demanded as a
                    matter of absolute right, not as a favor. <pb facs="0359" n="261"
                        xml:id="pg_261"/> Since the Chinese Government admits that it possesses the
                    power to give communication, it puts itself in an unfriendly attitude by denying
                    it. No negotiations seem advisable until the Chinese Government shall have put
                    the diplomatic representatives of the powers in full and free communication with
                    their respective Governments and removed all danger to their lives and liberty.
                    We would urge Earl Li earnestly to advise the Imperial authorities of China to
                    place themselves in friendly communication and cooperation with the relief
                    expedition. They are assuming a heavy responsibility in acting otherwise.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
